ns":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be dazzled, to be blinded, to have vision blocked","examples":[{"text":"يصولُ بمَجْرٍ لَيْسَ يُحْصى عديدُه\nويَسْدَرُ مِنْهُ، ساجِياً، كلُّ ناظِرِ","english":"He encroaches numerously in a number that cannot be counted\nAnd every beholder is silent and dazzled by him."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be careless, to be regardless, to be reckless"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to let go, to exert"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hung down, to descend"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَدِرَ (sadira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"buckthorn, trees of the genus Ziziphus","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"فِي سِدْرٍ مَّخْضُودٍ وَطَلْحٍ مَّنْضُودٍ","english":"[They will be] among buckthorn trees with thorns removed and vachellia trees layered [with fruit]"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Sense of letting go cognate with Hebrew שִׁדֵּר (shidér, “to send, to dispatch, to broadcast”) via Jewish Babylonian Aramaic root ש־ד־ר (“to send”)\n\nFrom the root س د ر (s d r) meaning “to obscure or block vision”, “to make an area inaccessible or blocked”; originally applied variously to lofty trees associated with shade."},"ipa":["/sa.di.ra/","/sidr/"]}